metadata.description:
"It was the best of times, it was the worst of times, it was the age of wisdom, it was the age of foolishness, it was the epoch of belief, it was the epoch of incredulity, it was the season of Light, it was the season of Darkness, it was the spring of hope, it was the winter of despair, we had everything before us, we had nothing before us..."

It is built entirely on thi.ng/umbrella libraries and template:

metadata.name: Limelight #114
metadata.description:
Inspired by repetitions, symmetry, and evolution in nature, Limelight is a series of moving structures symbolic of natural forms, that emphasize relationships between architectures, transport networks, and materials - all in thirst for light.

Tap anywhere on the artwork or press the space bar to start and stop the animation.

Created with GLSL and p5js. It is fully responsive to any screen size.

To all collectors, reach out on Twitter (@uditmahajan24) if you want a high-resolution image of your mint.

metadata.name: Fast Food Wall Art Simulation #104
metadata.description:
"Fast Food Wall Art Simulation" is created from many hidden circular drawings. 

I placed each drawing in a different hidden canvas and read its pixel values to approximate the texture of the circles. Technically that makes this an Image composition, but the images are never shown on the canvas.

I played around with different ways the circles could be overlapped. Differing opacity, blend modes, and pixel skipping were used to create some interesting textures.

In my testing, many of the renders, especially the more earth-tone ones, reminded me of art used in fast food restaurants in the 90s when I was growing up.

Features:
Four different sizes: 9x16, 11x14", 12x18", 12x12"
Portrait or landscape orientation
~500 color pallets, one black and white, one CMYK, one RGB, and the rest from Jam3/nice-color-palettes.

Dependencies:
processing/p5.js
lodash/lodash
Jam3/nice-color-palettes

Export to a PNG format at several different sizes.
- Press s: save the current render size
- Press t: scale to screen size
- Press f: full print size (see features for dimensions)

License: CC-BY

Please find me on Twitter and Instagram at @natenolting.

metadata.name: Sixty# #174
metadata.description:
This idea was born from recent discussion on generative art and the path the medium is finding for itself. The project aims to take aesthetic concepts from sci fi graphic novels and blend them with generative systems of abstraction. 

The debate is between using previously established art forms to influence this new medium, or using a new medium to meticulously reproduce a previous medium. I believe there’s room to explore the full spectrum, and I am attempting to find the midpoint that fits my work and brings me the most happiness.

The title describes the eventual aesthetic objective, which is to create a piece which might look like a splash page a colorist alone has been given the freedom to design and explore their own specialty. It explores centralized polar compositions, vibrant colors, plus lots and lots of movement. 60# paper is a standard weight for printing of comic books and graphic novels.

Press ’s’ in live view to save a .png

Created with p5.js and chroma.js

metadata.name: Sap song. Part II #123
metadata.description:
This artwork corresponds to the 2nd part of the ‘Sap song’ series. It seeks to expand the concept from new visual and sound variants.

Audiovisual generative artwork that continues with the proposal of excessive flows of organic forms. In time, frenetic arpeggios and populations of colorful plants with spiral flowers are emerging, all organized in their own way. And the sap again sings, feeds and shows us a constructive desire for afforestation.

The work has 3 moments:
I. “Enredo coral”
II. “Recitativo libre”
III. “Coda hacia la raíz”

Original samplers of cello pizzicatos, marimba, music box, piano, and multiphonics of clarinet and flute.

[ s ] -> save 2160x2160px (in live view)
[ f ] -> fullscreen

attributes.name: instruments:
attributes.value: cello, marimba, music box and flute

metadata.name: sketch: cairn() #23
metadata.description:
A cairn is a monument made of stacked rocks. In modern times, often used for wayfinding in remote areas, as in mountaineering, or to indicate an area of significance.

In this sketch I imagine these monuments -- through the looking glass. Paying mind to the simplicity of their construction, as well as the mysticism of what each might represent.

---

Sketch is a series meant to celebrate learning and experimentation.

In this sketch I experiment with subdivision, smoothing, textures, multiple levels of domain warping, and illustration techniques.

---
- Made with p5js
- Press s to save png
- Use param ?width=x to render at size
